Sure, here are some example sentences that use the word "priča" in different forms and positions:

1. *Priča* je veoma zanimljiva. (The *story* is very interesting.)
2. Ona voli da *priča* o svojim putovanjima. (She likes to *talk* about her travels.)
3. Mnogo je ljudi koji ne umeju da *pričaju* viceve. (There are many people who don't know how to *tell* jokes.)
4. *Pričaj* mi šta se desilo sinoć. (Tell me what happened last night.)
5. Naše bake su uvek imale dobre *priče* o nekadašnjem vremenu. (Our grandmothers always had good *stories* about the old times.)
6. Njihova *priča* nije istinita. (Their *story* is not true.)
7. Molim te, ne prekidaj moju *priču*. (Please don't interrupt my *story*.)
8. Da li znaš *priču* o Alisi u zemlji čuda? (Do you know the *story* of Alice in Wonderland?)

Note: In Serbian, the word "priča" can mean both "story" and "to tell/talk".